          "content": "Yes, exactly. The full round-trip for one motor is:\n\n```\nFPGA                    PCB                      Motor\n────                    ───                      ─────\nmotor[0] ──────────► H-bridge ──── wire A ────► motor coil\nmotor[1] ──────────► H-bridge ──── wire B ────► motor coil\n\nencoder[0] ◄──────────────────── enc A ◄─────── encoder chip\nencoder[1] ◄──────────────────── enc B ◄─────── encoder chip\n```\n\nThe encoder signals come straight back into the FPGA pins defined in the constraints file (e.g. `encoder0[0]` and `encoder0[1]`), which wire directly into `enc_in[0]` and `enc_in[1]` on the `motor_controller` block, which feeds the `quadDecoder`, which updates the 16-bit position counter, which the ARM reads back over AXI to close the PID loop."
        }
